-- US Ex-Im OKs $118 million loan for Vietnam to buy Lockheed satellite
-- 
-- Mon Oct 1, 2012 2:19pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/01/us-usa-vietnam-satellite-idUSBRE89016620121001

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The U.S. Export-Import Bank on Monday said it has approved an $118 million direct loan to a Vietnamese state-owned company to buy a telecommunications satellite and other goods and services from Lockheed Martin ( LMT.N ). 
 "By providing financing for Vietnam Posts and Telecommunications Group, this Ex-Im Bank loan supports U.S. manufactured satellites and U.S. jobs," Linda Reiners, a vice president at Lockheed Martin, said in a statement. (Reporting by  Doug Palmer ; Editing by  James Dalgleish )